{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":3556604,"name":"Krypton #9487","username":"NKRY_FRC","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/nkry_frc/{size}/206723_2.png","created_at":"2025-03-13T23:09:20.486Z","cooked":"<p>Hello everyone, today our regional training matches started, we played all the training matches in the blue alliance, and everything went well, but in our last training match we were in the red alliance, and the Joystick directions were inverted, can someone help me?</p>","post_number":1,"post_type":1,"posts_count":9,"updated_at":"2025-03-13T23:10:54.745Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":9,"reads":215,"readers_count":214,"score":88.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":495510,"topic_slug":"inverted-swerve-on-the-red-alliance","display_username":"Krypton #9487","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":60531,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":""},"post_url":"/t/inverted-swerve-on-the-red-alliance/495510/1","reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3556753,"name":"","username":"Hollisms","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/hollisms/{size}/110925_2.png","created_at":"2025-03-14T03:24:29.054Z","cooked":"<p>You need to invert your controls by multiplying the joystick input by -1 if your alliance is red.</p>
<p>Since you are pressed for time I would suggest you create a variable set it to 1 and multiply your left joystick axes (assuming you are swerve) by that variable.  Then map a joystick button to multiply that variable by -1. That way you can toggle it quickly.</p>
<p>When you have more time and depending on what drivetrain template you used there is a more elegant way.</p>","post_number":2,"post_type":1,"posts_count":9,"updated_at":"2025-03-14T03:25:34.101Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":1,"reads":188,"readers_count":187,"score":62.6,"yours":false,"topic_id":495510,"topic_slug":"inverted-swerve-on-the-red-alliance","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":1}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":36169,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"Software Mentor"},"post_url":"/t/inverted-swerve-on-the-red-alliance/495510/2","reactions":[{"id":"heart","type":"emoji","count":1}],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":1,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3556798,"name":"Justin Buist","username":"Justin_Buist","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/j/c77e96/{size}.png","created_at":"2025-03-14T05:07:59.182Z","cooked":"<p>Just check for wpilib.DriverStation.getAlliance() == wpilib.Driverstation.Alliance.kRed</p>
<p>If true, invert the x and y. You can put it right next to where you read the joystick inputs to keep it simple.</p>","post_number":3,"post_type":1,"posts_count":9,"updated_at":"2025-03-14T05:07:59.182Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":2,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":139,"readers_count":138,"score":32.8,"yours":false,"topic_id":495510,"topic_slug":"inverted-swerve-on-the-red-alliance","display_username":"Justin Buist","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","reply_to_user":{"id":36169,"username":"Hollisms","name":"","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/hollisms/{size}/110925_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":24678,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"post_url":"/t/inverted-swerve-on-the-red-alliance/495510/3","reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3556838,"name":"","username":"Hollisms","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/hollisms/{size}/110925_2.png","created_at":"2025-03-14T10:16:07.116Z","cooked":"<p>Yes…. But keep in mind that returns an optional so when/where/how that code is executed is important because the value can change. Depending on how the reset gyro/IMU function works it may have unintended consequences.  Also, if they are using Pathplanner or something to seed an orientation during autonomous that could have unintended consequences.</p>
<p>So, I agree with you but my “hack” suggestion is provided as something easy to test and the driver can “revert” easily.</p>","post_number":4,"post_type":1,"posts_count":9,"updated_at":"2025-03-14T10:16:07.116Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":3,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":105,"readers_count":104,"score":36.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":495510,"topic_slug":"inverted-swerve-on-the-red-alliance","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","reply_to_user":{"id":24678,"username":"Justin_Buist","name":"Justin Buist","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/j/c77e96/{size}.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":1}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":36169,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"Software Mentor"},"post_url":"/t/inverted-swerve-on-the-red-alliance/495510/4","reactions":[{"id":"heart","type":"emoji","count":1}],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":1,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3556926,"name":"","username":"CarbonSmasher","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/carbonsmasher/{size}/255012_2.png","created_at":"2025-03-14T13:33:41.637Z","cooked":"<p>You need to pass in a gyro angle that is relative to your alliance wall to the <code>ChassisSpeeds.fromFieldRelativeSpeeds()</code> function. This means 0 degrees is facing away from your alliance wall.</p>","post_number":5,"post_type":1,"posts_count":9,"updated_at":"2025-03-14T13:33:41.637Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":61,"readers_count":60,"score":17.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":495510,"topic_slug":"inverted-swerve-on-the-red-alliance","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":62692,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"post_url":"/t/inverted-swerve-on-the-red-alliance/495510/5","reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3556931,"name":"","username":"griffingreat1","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/g/71e660/{size}.png","created_at":"2025-03-14T13:41:55.523Z","cooked":"<p>The way to fix this to invert the input from the controller joystick responsible for x/y motion in the drive function (do not invert the rotation value, this remains constant because clockwise is still clockwise no matter your orientation). this is the way I recommend doing it. the reason you do this is because the “origin” of the field is always on the blue side, and so whatever inputs you give while on red will still be relative to the blue driver station. Our team uses AdvantageKit, so if your team does not, remove the last argument of the if statement. We had this exact same issue last year (last year was our first year using swerve and pathplanner), and this was the best fix we found. In response to <a class="mention" href="/u/hollisms">@Hollisms</a> reply, my team uses pathplanner, and this worked for us just fine.</p>
<pre><code class="lang-auto">public void drive(double xSpeed, double ySpeed, double rot, boolean fieldRelative, boolean rateLimit) {
        if (DriverStation.getAlliance().isPresent() &amp;&amp; DriverStation.getAlliance().get() == Alliance.Red &amp;&amp; AdvantageKitConstants.getMode()==Mode.REAL) {
            xSpeed = -xSpeed;
            ySpeed = -ySpeed;
        }
        // the rest of your drive function.
}
</code></pre>
<p>here is a little diagram if it helps:<br>
